{"lemma":"لُبُّ","slug":"لُبُّ","root":"ل.ب.ب","root_slug":"ل-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37426","n37427"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pulp, backlog, marrow, core, heart"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"intellect, discernment"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stay, to bide, to persevere"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be intelligent, to be smart"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Inherited from Proto-Semitic *libb- (“heart”), from Proto-Afroasiatic *lib-.\nCognate with Hebrew לב (lev) and Classical Syriac ܠܒܐ (lebbā)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37426","headword_ar":"لَبٌّ","root":"lb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~a","text_ar":"لَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he remained, &c. ” ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lb~ayoka","text_ar":"لبَّيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At thy service!"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Doubly at thy service!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~ayohi","text_ar":"لَبَّيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At his service: &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marohuwbN","text_ar":"مَرْهُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". It is used in the present day like our phrase"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At thy service,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and may well be thus rendered, or with the addition of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time after time."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lb~yk","text_ar":"لبّيك"},{"kind":"text","text":"is derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alab~a","text_ar":"اَلَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~a","text_ar":"لَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alb~","text_ar":"البّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] “ he remained &c. ”; and means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I wait intent upon thy service,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon obedience to thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waiting"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at they service"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after waiting;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time after time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and answering"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy commands"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after answering:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) it [i. e. the noun without the annexed pron.] is put in the acc. case as an inf. n. [used as an absolute complement of its own verb which is understood], as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamodFA lil~`hi w$ukorFA","text_ar":"حَمْدًا لِلّٰهِ وشُكْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the right way would be to say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~FA laka","text_ar":"لَبًّا لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but it is put in the dual number for the sake of corroboration; meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilobaAbFA","text_ar":"اـِلْبَابًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bika baEoda A_ilobaAbK","text_ar":"بِكَ بَعْدَ اـِلْبَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iqaAmapF baEoda A_iqaAmapK","text_ar":"اـِقَامَةً بَعْدَ اـِقَامَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waiting at thy service,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in attendance upon thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in thy presence, after waiting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time after time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Fr, S.) [See also the similar expression"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEodayoka","text_ar":"سَعْدَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~N","text_ar":"لَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obeying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"serving;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obedience,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"service;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from the original signification of the “ remaining, staying, abiding, or dwelling, ” [in a place]: the dual, in the nom. case, is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~Ani","text_ar":"لَبّانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in the acc. and gen.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~ayoni","text_ar":"لَبَّيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the original meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lbyk","text_ar":"لبيك"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have obeyed thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"served thee, twice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I do obey thee, &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lb~yn","text_ar":"لبّين"},{"kind":"text","text":"] being elided because of its being prefixed to the pron. (IAar.) Or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lb~yk","text_ar":"لبّيك"},{"kind":"text","text":"is from the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAru fulaAnK talub~u daAriY","text_ar":"دَارُ فُلَانٍ تَلُبُّ دَارِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ the house of such a one faces my house ”; (Kh, S, K;) and the meaning is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I present myself before thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repair to thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doing what thou likest, answering thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after answering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time after time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is to form the dual number; and indicates that the noun is in the acc. case as an inf. n. [used as mentioned above]. (Kh, S.) Or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My love"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is given"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from the expression"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN lab~apN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ لَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ a woman loving (and affectionate, TA,) to her husband ”: so in the K: but the expression, as related on the authority of Kh, is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~N lab~apN","text_ar":"اُمٌّ لَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which is confirmed by a verse that he cites. (TA.) Or the meaning is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ixolaASiY laka","text_ar":"اـِخْلَاصِى لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My sincere service,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is given"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] from the expression"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasabN lubaAbN","text_ar":"حَسَبٌ لُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ pure nobility, or the like. ” (K.) Accord. to Yoo,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lb~yk","text_ar":"لبّيك"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a noun in the sing. number with the pron. annexed to it: this noun is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~abN","text_ar":"لَبَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolalN","text_ar":"فَعْلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (not of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faE~alN","text_ar":"فَعَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because this is rare in the language:) the the last"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"to avoid the reduplication; and thus it becomes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~aYN","text_ar":"لَبَّىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": then the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", being movent, and immediately preceded by fet-hah, is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and it becomes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~aA","text_ar":"لَبَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~aY","text_ar":"لَبَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this case is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: then, being conjoined with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lb~yk","text_ar":"لبّيك"},{"kind":"text","text":", and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lb~yh","text_ar":"لبّيه"},{"kind":"text","text":", its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; after the same manner as you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayoka","text_ar":"اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayoka","text_ar":"عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ladayoka","text_ar":"لَدَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [But see what here follows.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~aYo","text_ar":"لَبَّىْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadayoka","text_ar":"يَدَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a phrase exactly similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lb~yk","text_ar":"لبّيك"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At the service"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or, lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doubly at the service"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of thy hands!"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is said, in the S, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lbY","text_ar":"لبى"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be at variance with the opinion of Yoo, given above; for, if"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lb~Y","text_ar":"لبّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"were similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., being prefixed to a noun, not a pron., it would be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~aY yadayoka","text_ar":"لَبَّى يَدَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~aYo","text_ar":"لَبَّىْ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Accord. to El-Khattá- bee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lb~Y ydyk","text_ar":"لبّى يديك"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May thy hands be safe and sound!"},{"kind":"text","text":"the desinential syntax being disregarded in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ydyk","text_ar":"يديك"},{"kind":"text","text":", which rightly should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadaAka","text_ar":"يَدَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in order that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ydyk","text_ar":"يديك"},{"kind":"text","text":"may match in sound with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lb~yk","text_ar":"لبّيك"},{"kind":"text","text":": but Z says, that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will obey thee, and be at thy free disposal, as a thing which thou shalt dispose of with thy hands in whatever manner thou shalt please."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  In like manner you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~aYo zayodK","text_ar":"لَبَّىْ زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At the service"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doubly at the service"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lbY","text_ar":"لبى"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~i","text_ar":"لَبِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesreh for its termination, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amos","text_ar":"اَمْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAqi","text_ar":"غَاقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is also related as having been used: (Sb:) [and it is still used in some parts, as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At thy service!"},{"kind":"text","text":"].       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~N","text_ar":"لَبٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keeping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adhering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to a thing]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remaining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"staying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A camel-driver who keeps constantly to the work of driving the camels, not leaving them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN lab~N","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ لَبٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who keeps to a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"business;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labiybN","text_ar":"لَبِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man who keeps to his art,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"craft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trade, not ceasing from it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rjlN lab~N Tab~N","text_ar":"رجلٌ لَبٌّ طَبٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who keeps to business,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and is skilful, expert, clever,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab","text_ar":"لَب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who renders himself near to people by affection and friendship"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is friendly and affectionate to them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"courteous, polite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affable:"},{"kind":"text","text":"fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~apN","text_ar":"لَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libaAbN","text_ar":"لِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN lab~apN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ لَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman who renders herself near by affection"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2643},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and friendship"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is friendly and affectionate"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to people;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"courteous, polite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affable:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman loving to her husband;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affectionate to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Kh, the expression is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~N lab~apN","text_ar":"اُمٌّ لَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~N","text_ar":"لَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", above. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Sb","S"]},{"entry_id":"n37427","headword_ar":"لُبٌّ","root":"lb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lubaAbN","text_ar":"لُبَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) of a nut, an almond, and the like,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is in the inside;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kernel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) of a palm-tree, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pith,"},{"kind":"text","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalobN","text_ar":"قَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qulobN","text_ar":"قُلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) Pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lubuwbN","text_ar":"لُبُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lub~N","text_ar":"لُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lubaAbN","text_ar":"لُبَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is pure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"choice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best, part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything: (S, K:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alobaAbN","text_ar":"اَلْبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A'Obeyd.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lub~u AlHinoTapi","text_ar":"لُبُّ الحِنْطَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The purest substance of wheat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAluw*N","text_ar":"فَالُوذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] (T, L, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fl*","text_ar":"فلذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c:) [also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albur~i","text_ar":"البُرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lubaAbu","text_ar":"لُبَابُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", acc. to Sprenger, “ Life of Mohammad, ” (Allahabad, 1851,) p. 24, note 1.] ―         -b4-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lub~N","text_ar":"لُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man, (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Understanding; intellect; intelligence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqolN","text_ar":"عَقْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"understanding, &c., that is put into the heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man: so called because it is the choicest or best part of him: or it is not so called unless it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pure from cupidity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lust, and foul imaginations;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and therefore has a more special sense than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eql","text_ar":"عقل"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the Keshf el-Keshsháf: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alobaAbN","text_ar":"اَلْبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alub~N","text_ar":"اَلُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abow^usN","text_ar":"اَبْوُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buw^osN","text_ar":"بُوْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoEumN","text_ar":"اَنْعُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuEomN","text_ar":"نُعْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alobubN","text_ar":"اَلْبُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) the last being used, without incorporating the second"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"into the first, in case of necessity in poetry. (S.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu A^alobubK","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ اَلْبُبٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain veins in the heart; the sources of tenderness, affection, kindness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compassion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^obaY lahu *`lika banaAtu A^alobubiY","text_ar":"تَاْبَى لَهُ ذٰلِكَ بَنَاتُ اَلْبُبِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My tenderness forbids the doing so to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: said by an Arab woman of the desert, on the occasion of her reproving her son, to one who asked her why she did not curse him. (S.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloqaY Ealayohi banaAta A^alobubihi","text_ar":"اَلْقَى عَلَيْهِ بَنَاتَ اَلْبُبِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He loved it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$r","text_ar":"شر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b8-  The following words of the poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qado Ealimato *aAka banaAtu A^alobubiho"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify, accord. to the M,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My intellect knew that."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) El-Mubarrad read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alobabiho","text_ar":"اَلْبَبِهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the above words of the poet: (TA:) the meaning of these words, accord. to him, is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The daughters of the most intelligent of his tribe knew this."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b9-  If you form a pl. from [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alobubN","text_ar":"اَلْبُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alaAbibu","text_ar":"اَلَابِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the dim. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ulayobibN","text_ar":"اُلَيْبِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw lub~K","text_ar":"ذُو لُبٍّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Possessing, having,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person of, understanding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwluwA A@loA^alobaAbi","text_ar":"اُولُوا ا@لْاَلْبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persons of understandings"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labiybN","text_ar":"لَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malobuwbN","text_ar":"مَلْبُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lub~N","text_ar":"لُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"self, substance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"essence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Poison:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poison of the serpent"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes thus called. (Abu-l-Hasan, L.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lub~N","text_ar":"لُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the dial. of El-Andalus and El-'Adweh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain beast of prey, resembling the wolf, said by AHei not to exist in other countries."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb","TA"]}]}}